perature as we probe longer PACS and SPIRE\nwavelengths. These results may have important implications for the use of\nmonochromatic dust luminosity as a star formation rate indicator in\nstar-forming galaxies, and in the future, for using radio data to determine\ngalaxy star formation rates.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 8 Sep 2014 20:00:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-22"}
