 by ($q=\\frac{9}{10},~~N=70$). Also there is a range of values of $R$\nand $n_s$ which is compatible with the BICEP2 data where $q=\\frac{9}{10}$. In\ncase $\\Gamma=\\Gamma_1V(\\phi)$, it is observed that small values of a number of\ne-folds are assured for small values of $q$ parameter. For $q=\\frac{9}{10}$ a\nrange of values of $R$ and $n_s$ is compatible with the BICEP2 data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 9 Sep 2014 12:00:28 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 30 Jun 2015 11:43:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-09"}
